# The Elder Council and Imperial Governance

The **Elder Council** is the oldest and most enduring political institution of the **Empire of Tamriel**. Founded under the Alessian Empire, it survived the fall of three Imperial dynasties, weathered the **Interregnum**, and continues to function under the Mede Empire in the Fourth Era. It represents Imperial administrative continuity beyond individual sovereigns.

## Structure

### Composition

The Elder Council is composed of:
- **The Chancellor** (High Chancellor): president of the Council, often the most powerful figure after the Emperor
- **The Councilors**: nobles, scholars, and administrators appointed by the Emperor or co-opted
- **The Potentate**: title used during regencies and periods without an emperor

The exact number of councilors varies by era — from a few dozen under the Alessians to more than a hundred under the Septims.

### Powers

Under normal circumstances, the Council:
- Advises the Emperor on affairs of state
- Administers the provinces on behalf of the crown
- Ratifies treaties and declarations of war
- Manages Imperial finances and tax collection
- Oversees the Imperial Legions and their deployment

In the event of a **vacant throne**, the Council becomes the supreme authority:
- It acts as regent under the title of Potentate
- It organizes the succession (often with great difficulty)
- It can theoretically elect a new Emperor if no heir exists

## Political history

### Under the Alessian Empire (1E 243 — 1E 2331)

The Council was created by **Alessia** herself to govern the nascent Empire after the liberation of humans from **Ayleid** slavery. At this time, it combined religious and political functions — priests of the Alessian Order sat alongside nobles.

### The Akaviri Potentate (1E 2920 — 2E 430)

After the assassination of the last **Reman** emperor, power passed to the **Akaviri Potentate** — first Versidue-Shaie, then his son Savirien-Chorak. The Council governed under their authority for five centuries, a testament to its institutional resilience.

### The Interregnum (2E 430 — 2E 854)

The assassination of Savirien-Chorak and his entire lineage in 2E 430 plunged the Empire into chaos. Without an Emperor or Potentate, the Council fragmented into rival factions:

<CausalChain items={[
  { text: "Assassination of the Akaviri Potentate (2E 430)" },
  { text: "Fragmentation of the Council into provincial factions", indent: 1 },
